<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Change on Valticus</title><link>https://valticus.pro/tags/change/</link><description>Recent content in Change on Valticus</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 04 Apr 2021 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://valticus.pro/tags/change/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>How To Change Your GitHub Theme</title><link>https://valticus.pro/posts/how-to-change-your-github-theme/</link><pubDate>Sun, 04 Apr 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://valticus.pro/posts/how-to-change-your-github-theme/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;So, as you may or may not know, &lt;a href="https://github.com/"&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt; is testing themes for its website, and the feature is now in beta according to &lt;a href="https://docs.github.com/en/github/setting-up-and-managing-your-github-user-account/managing-your-theme-settings"&gt;GitHub Docs&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To change how your &lt;a href="https://github.com/"&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt; looks, you need to log in to your &lt;a href="https://github.com/"&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt; account, click your profile pictures, choose &lt;em&gt;Settings&lt;/em&gt; &amp;gt; &lt;em&gt;Appearance&lt;/em&gt; and on the section that opens, choose one of the three themes that are currently available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Below are the screen shots, courtesy of &lt;a href="https://docs.github.com/en/github/setting-up-and-managing-your-github-user-account/managing-your-theme-settings"&gt;GitHub Docs&lt;/a&gt;:
